HEADWORD: Compressible
<hw>Com*press"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>compressible</ets>.]</ety> <def>Capable of being pressed together
or forced into a narrower compass, as an elastic or spongy
substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Compressibleness</ent>⟦br⟧
